olive oil
1 potato
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
2 packet chicken breast
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 tsp soy sauce
1 stalk celery
1 bag Slaw Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 tsp sesame oil
1 bag parsley
drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place peeled pumpkin pieces and potato on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
• In a medium bowl, combine sweet soy seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil. Add chicken and turn to coat.
• When the veggies have 10 minutes remaining, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook chicken in batches until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove pan from heat, return all chicken and add sweet chilli sauce and the soy sauce, turning chicken to coat.

TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice celery.
• In a second medium bowl, combine slaw mix, celery, mayonnaise, the sesame oil and a drizzle of vinegar. Season to taste.

Little cooks: Help toss the slaw.

• Divide sweet soy-glazed chicken, celery slaw and roast veggie chunks between plates. Tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Help tear over the parsley.